data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**EF Core 11 fully removes sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async — in .NET 11 that opt-in is gone. Every synchronous call (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) **always throws** at runtime. There is no workaround; you must go async.

Your repository needs to become:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
- Return types become `Task<T>` / `Task`
- Methods become `async` and use `await`
- Rename with `Async` suffix (convention)
- **All callers** up the call chain must also be updated to `await`

This is a **medium-impact** breaking change tracked at [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
